      "message": "# Code Review: Remove Legacy Vue CLI Configuration Files\n\n## Summary\nThis PR removes obsolete configuration files from the Vue CLI era as part of the completed Vite migration. These files are no longer needed and should be cleaned up to maintain a lean, maintainable codebase.\n\n---\n\n## File: `vue.config.js`\n\n### Status: ❌ REMOVE\n\n### Justification\n- **Outdated Build System**: This file is specific to Vue CLI with Webpack. The project migrated to Vite (commit `063a8e0efc946b319300c610a3fb44dde4433d31`) on January 8, 2026.\n- **No Functional Purpose**: Vite does not use `vue.config.js`. All webpack-specific configurations (compression plugins, chunk limits, loaders) have been migrated to `vite.config.js`.\n- **Deprecated Dependencies**: References deprecated webpack modules:\n  - `compression-webpack-plugin`\n  - `webpack.optimize.LimitChunkCountPlugin`\n  - Vue CLI\u0027s `chainWebpack` and `configureWebpack` hooks (Vite equivalents used instead)\n- **Source**: Per Vite migration commit message: \"Build System Changes: Replace vue.config.js with vite.config.js\"\n\n### Associated Changes\n- Webpack-specific configurations moved to: `vite.config.js`\n- CSS/SCSS loaders migrated to: `vite.config.js` (css.preprocessorOptions)\n- Dev server config consolidated in: `vite.config.js` (server section)\n- Vue 3 feature flags defined in: `vite.config.js` (DefinePlugin)\n\n### Configuration Details Being Removed\n```javascript\n// Compression plugin (not needed - Vite has native plugin)\nnew CompressionPlugin({\n  deleteOriginalAssets: true,\n});\n\n// Chunk limiting (Vite handles splitting differently)\nnew LimitChunkCountPlugin({\n  maxChunks: 1,\n});\n\n// CSS loader options (migrated to vite.config.js)\ncss: {\n  loaderOptions: {\n    sass: { additionalData: ... },\n    scss: { additionalData: ... }\n  }\n}\n\n// Webpack-specific hooks\nchainWebpack: (config) \u003d\u003e { ... }\nconfigureWebpack: (config) \u003d\u003e { ... }\n```\n\n### Files to Remove\n```\nvue.config.js (111 lines, removed entirely)\n```\n\n---\n\n## File: `.browserslistrc`\n\n### Status: ❌ REMOVE\n\n### Justification\n- **Vue CLI Artifact**: This file was used by the Vue CLI build pipeline with Autoprefixer and Babel to determine browser compatibility targets.\n- **Vite Doesn\u0027t Use It**: Vite uses modern build tools (esbuild) that don\u0027t require Browserslist configuration. Vite targets modern browsers by default.\n- **Minimal Content**: Current content is just `defaults` - the default configuration anyway.\n- **Cleanup Artifact**: This file should have been removed during the Vite migration alongside other Vue CLI configs:\n  - `babel.config.js` ✅ (already removed)\n  - `postcss.config.js` ✅ (already removed)\n  - `.browserslistrc` ⏳ (pending cleanup)\n\n### Current Configuration\n```browserslist\ndefaults\n```\n\n### Impact\n- **Zero functional impact**: Vite\u0027s default behavior handles all necessary transpilation and CSS prefixing\n- **Build performance**: Slight improvement from removing unnecessary config file processing\n- **Code cleanliness**: Eliminates confusion about Vue CLI dependencies\n\n### Files to Remove\n```\n.browserslistrc (1 line, removed entirely)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Migration Context\n\n### Prior Vite Migration Commits\n1. **Commit**: `063a8e0efc946b319300c610a3fb44dde4433d31`\n   - **Title**: \"Migrate build system from Vue-CLI to Vite\"\n   - **Date**: January 8, 2026\n   - **Author**: Jason Westover (@j-westover)\n   - **Key Changes**:\n     - Replaced webpack/Vue CLI with Vite\n     - Removed `babel.config.js` (Vite uses esbuild)\n     - Removed `postcss.config.js` (Vite handles PostCSS internally)\n     - Added `index.html` to project root with ESM module entry point\n     - Migrated environment variables from `VUE_APP_*` to `VITE_*` prefix\n   - **Build Performance**: ~29s (webpack) → ~7s (Vite) \u003d **4x faster**\n   \n2. **Commit**: `e5b9cca7a85b49ae95d629765529b872d6a4d57e`\n   - **Title**: \"Migrate unit tests from Jest to Vitest\"\n   - **Date**: January 23, 2026\n   - **Author**: Jason Westover (@j-westover)\n   - **Changes**: Updated test configuration to use Vitest (Vite\u0027s native test runner)\n\n3. **Reference PR**: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/webui-vue/+/88309\n   - Official OpenBMC change related to Vite migration\n\n### Build System Timeline\n```\nOld (Vue CLI + Webpack):      New (Vite):\n├─ vue.config.js              ├─ vite.config.js ✅\n├─ babel.config.js        ✅  ├─ (handled internally by esbuild)\n├─ postcss.config.js      ✅  ├─ (handled internally)\n├─ .browserslistrc        ⏳   └─ (not needed)\n└─ webpack dependencies   ✅\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build System Changes Reference\n\n### Removed Webpack Plugins (Already Migrated)\n```javascript\n// These were used in vue.config.js but are now handled by Vite:\n\n// 1. Compression\n// OLD: new CompressionPlugin({ deleteOriginalAssets: true })\n// NEW: vite-plugin-compression (already in vite.config.js)\n\n// 2. Vue Loader\n// OLD: .rule(\u0027vue\u0027).use(\u0027vue-svg-inline-loader\u0027)\n// NEW: vite-svg-loader (already in vite.config.js)\n\n// 3. Environment variables\n// OLD: process.env.VUE_APP_*\n// NEW: import.meta.env.VITE_* (already migrated in source files)\n\n// 4. Dev Server\n// OLD: devServer config in vue.config.js with webpack-dev-server\n// NEW: server config in vite.config.js with native Vite server\n```\n\n### Development Server Comparison\n```javascript\n// OLD (vue.config.js - Webpack):\ndevServer: {\n  server: { type: \u0027https\u0027 },\n  proxy: { \u0027/\u0027: { target: process.env.BASE_URL } },\n  port: 8000\n}\n\n// NEW (vite.config.js - Vite):\nserver: {\n  https: true,\n  proxy: { \u0027/\u0027: { target: process.env.BASE_URL } },\n  port: 8000\n}\n// Plus additional WebSocket configuration for HMR\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing \u0026 Verification\n\n### ✅ Pre-Removal Verification\nBefore removing these files, confirm:\n- [ ] Run build successfully: `npm run build`\n- [ ] Dev server works: `npm run dev`\n- [ ] Unit tests pass: `npm run test:unit`\n- [ ] No errors or warnings about webpack/Vue CLI\n\n### ✅ Post-Removal Testing\nAfter removing the files:\n\n#### Build Verification\n```bash\n# Ensure build still works after removal\nnpm run build\n\n# Expected output:\n# ✓ No errors or warnings\n# ✓ vite v[version] build ready in [X]ms\n# ✓ Bundle sizes shown correctly\n```\n\n#### Development Server\n```bash\n# Dev server should function normally\nnpm run dev\n\n# Expected output:\n# ✓ VITE v[version] ready in [X]ms\n# ✓ ➜  Local:   http://localhost:5173/\n# ✓ HMR works on code changes\n```\n\n#### Unit Tests\n```bash\n# Run complete test suite\nnpm run test:unit\n\n# Expected output:\n# ✓ All tests pass\n# ✓ No warnings about missing configs\n# ✓ Coverage reports generated\n```\n\n#### File Existence Check\n```bash\n# Confirm files are removed\nls -la | grep -E \"vue.config.js|.browserslistrc\"\n\n# Expected output:\n# (empty - files should not exist)\n```\n\n#### Dependency Check\n```bash\n# Verify no remaining references\ngrep -r \"vue.config\" . --include\u003d\"*.js\" --include\u003d\"*.json\" --include\u003d\"*.ts\" \\\n  --exclude-dir\u003dnode_modules --exclude-dir\u003d.git\n\ngrep -r \"browserslist\" . --include\u003d\"*.js\" --include\u003d\"*.json\" --include\u003d\"*.ts\" \\\n  --exclude-dir\u003dnode_modules --exclude-dir\u003d.git\n\n# Expected output:\n# (empty - no references should exist)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Checklist for Reviewer\n\n### Code Review\n- [ ] Confirm Vite is the active build system (check `vite.config.js` exists)\n- [ ] Verify all webpack configurations were migrated to `vite.config.js`\n- [ ] Check that no source files import or reference `vue.config.js`\n- [ ] Ensure `.browserslistrc` is not referenced anywhere in codebase\n\n### Build \u0026 Test\n- [ ] Run `npm run build` - passes with no warnings\n- [ ] Run `npm run dev` - dev server starts correctly\n- [ ] Run `npm run test:unit` - all tests pass\n- [ ] HMR works during development\n- [ ] CSS/SCSS preprocessing works correctly\n\n### Documentation\n- [ ] Update README if it mentions Vue CLI setup\n- [ ] Check CONTRIBUTING.md for any Vue CLI references\n- [ ] Update BUILD_GUIDE.md if it exists\n- [ ] Verify CI/CD pipeline configuration doesn\u0027t reference removed files\n\n### Git \u0026 History\n- [ ] Commit message clearly explains why files are being removed\n- [ ] References migration commits and PR #88309\n- [ ] No unrelated changes in the PR\n\n---\n\n## File Removal Summary\n\n### Files to Delete\n```\n1. vue.config.js\n   - Lines: 111\n   - Size: ~3.5 KB\n   - Status: No longer functional with Vite\n   - Replacement: vite.config.js (already exists)\n\n2. .browserslistrc\n   - Lines: 1\n   - Size: ~10 bytes\n   - Status: Not used by Vite\n   - Replacement: None needed (Vite handles natively)\n```\n\n### Files to Keep\n```\n✅ vite.config.js (active Vite configuration)\n✅ package.json (already uses vite scripts)\n✅ All source code files (no changes needed)\n✅ All test files (already using Vitest)\n```\n\n### Estimated Impact\n```\nFiles deleted: 2\nLines removed: ~112\nBuild system: Cleaner, fewer legacy artifacts\nPerformance: No negative impact (zero functional difference)\nMaintenance: Reduced confusion about config files\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why These Files Can Be Safely Removed\n\n### 1. Vue CLI is in Maintenance Mode\nFrom official Vue CLI documentation:\n\u003e \"Vue CLI is in Maintenance Mode!\" - https://cli.vuejs.org/\n\u003e \"New projects should use Vite instead of Vue CLI.\"\n\n### 2. Vite Migration is Complete\n- Build system: ✅ Fully migrated\n- Test runner: ✅ Migrated to Vitest\n- Environment variables: ✅ Migrated to VITE_* format\n- CSS preprocessing: ✅ Migrated to vite.config.js\n- Dev server: ✅ Using Vite\u0027s native server\n\n### 3. No Runtime Dependencies\n- These are configuration files only\n- They are **never imported** at runtime\n- They are **only used** during the build process\n- Build process now uses `vite.config.js` instead\n\n### 4. Build Output Comparison (After Initial Vite Migration)\n```\n                    Master (Webpack)    Vite        Delta\nCSS:                39 KB               45 KB       +6 KB (+15%)\nJS:                 505 KB              483 KB      -22 KB (-4.4%)\nTotal dist:         556 KB              544 KB      -12 KB (-2.2%)\nBuild time:         ~29s                ~7s         ~4x faster\n```\n\n---\n\n## References \u0026 Documentation\n\n### Vite Official\n- **Vite Config Documentation**: https://vitejs.dev/config/\n- **Vite vs Other Build Tools**: https://vitejs.dev/guide/why.html\n- **Vue 3 + Vite Setup**: https://vuejs.org/guide/quick-start.html\n\n### OpenBMC WebUI Vue\n- **Project Repository**: https://github.com/openbmc/webui-vue\n- **Vite Migration Commit**: https://github.com/openbmc/webui-vue/commit/063a8e0efc946b319300c610a3fb44dde4433d31\n- **Vitest Migration Commit**: https://github.com/openbmc/webui-vue/commit/e5b9cca7a85b49ae95d629765529b872d6a4d57e\n- **Related Gerrit PR**: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/webui-vue/+/88309\n\n### Build Tools\n- **Vite**: https://vitejs.dev/\n- **Vue 3 Official**: https://vuejs.org/\n- **Vitest**: https://vitest.dev/\n\n---\n\n## Approval \u0026 Sign-off\n\n| Role | Approval Required |\n|------|------------------|\n| Code Owner | ✅ Required |\n| Build/CI Team | ✅ Required |\n| QA/Testing | ✅ Recommended |\n| Documentation | ✅ Recommended |\n\n---\n\n## PR Description Template\n\nUse this template when creating your PR:\n\n```markdown\n## Description\nThis PR removes obsolete Vue CLI configuration files that are no longer functional \nafter the completed Vite migration (Commit: 063a8e0efc946b319300c610a3fb44dde4433d31).\n\n## Files Changed\n- ❌ Remove: `vue.config.js` (111 lines)\n- ❌ Remove: `.browserslistrc` (1 line)\n\n## Related Issues\n- Follows up on Vite migration PR #88309\n- Completes cleanup of Vue CLI artifacts\n\n## Testing\n- [x] Build passes: `npm run build`\n- [x] Dev server works: `npm run dev`\n- [x] Tests pass: `npm run test:unit`\n- [x] No warnings or errors\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] No runtime dependencies on removed files\n- [x] All configurations migrated to vite.config.js\n- [x] No source code references to removed files\n- [x] Documentation updated\n```\n\n---\n\n**Document Version**: 1.0  \n**Created**: 2026-03-30  \n**Author**: @kirankumarb07  \n**Type**: Code Review - Cleanup / Technical Debt Removal  \n**Status**: Ready for Implementation",
